original: Kempe, Gustav Sigurd, prakt, läkare, Emmaboda, f. 26/9/99 i Bjurholm, Västerb. i., av prov:läk. Sven Gideon Leopold K. o. Anna Bernhardina Olsson. G. 36 m. Brita Reutercrona. Barn: Nils Gustav f. 37. — Stud:ex. i Skara 20, med. kand. 25 o. med. lic. 30 i Sthlm. Kort. förordn. s. e. läk. v. Gbgs hosp. 28 o. 30, i Delsbo distr. 30, s. stadsläk. i Marstrand 30 samt s. prov:läk. i Trosa, Bredbyns, Melle-ruds o. Gustavsbergs distr. 31, assist :-läk. v. Växjö las. 31, aman. v. Kronpr. Lovisas vårdanst. kir. avd. 32, assist :-läk. v. barnsjukh. Samariten 32-33, förordn. s. prov:läk. i Svenljunga, Ho-verbergs o. Haimimerdals distr, 33, tf. und:läk. v. Spenshults san. s. å., assist :läk. v. Östersunds las. 34, andre und:läk. v. Kolmårdssan. 34-35, und:-läk. v. Tranås kuranst. 35-36, prakt, läk. först i Nybro o. numera i Emmaboda. Bat:läk, v. Hälsinge reg. 42-44.
translated: Kempe, Gustav Sigurd, physician, Emmaboda, born on September 26, 1899 in Bjurholm, Västerbotten county, son of district physician Sven Gideon Leopold K. and Anna Bernhardina Olsson. Married in 1936 to Brita Reutercrona. Children: Nils Gustav, born in 1937. Completed high school in Skara in 1920, obtained Bachelor of Medicine degree in 1925, and medical license in 1930 in Stockholm. Briefly appointed as a medical intern at Gothenburg Hospital in 1928 and 1930, in the Delsbo district in 1930, as a city physician in Marstrand in 1930, and as a district physician in Trosa, Bredbyn, Mellerud, and Gustavsberg districts in 1931. Assistant physician at Växjö Hospital in 1931, assistant at Crown Princess Lovisa's Care Facility surgical department in 1932, assistant physician at Samariten Children's Hospital from 1932 to 1933, temporary district physician in Svenljunga, Hoverberg, and Haimimerdal districts in 1933, acting deputy physician at Spenshult Sanatorium in the same year, assistant physician at Östersund Hospital in 1934, deputy physician at Kolmården Sanatorium from 1934 to 1935, deputy physician at Tranås Spa from 1935 to 1936, and practicing physician first in Nybro and currently in Emmaboda. Battalion physician at Hälsinge Regiment from 1942 to 1944.
